Anything I need to know about?

67
00:04:04,130 --> 00:04:06,297
Nothin' I can't handle

68
00:04:06,297 --> 00:04:08,023
So you'll get back to me

69
00:04:08,023 --> 00:04:10,310
Definitely

70
00:04:12,741 --> 00:04:14,515
Thanks Lieutenant

71
00:04:16,781 --> 00:04:18,863
According to the lab,
baby Jane Doe's

72
00:04:18,863 --> 00:04:21,447
been at the bottom of this river
for forty-some years

73
00:04:21,447 --> 00:04:23,617
Puttin' her murder some time
in the 60's

74
00:04:23,617 --> 00:04:25,193
But from '60 to '69

75
00:04:25,193 --> 00:04:28,277
we got no missing persons report
of a 3 to 5 year old white female

76
00:04:28,277 --> 00:04:31,086
What kind of family
doesn't report their kid missing?

77
00:04:31,086 --> 00:04:33,842
The kind of family that kills their kid?

78
00:04:33,842 --> 00:04:36,829
Maybe we check DHS's
child abuse unit records

79
00:04:36,829 --> 00:04:38,922
Kid's doctor might've reported
that broken arm

80
00:04:38,922 --> 00:04:41,133
There was no Child Abuse Unit
back then

81
00:04:41,133 --> 00:04:44,239
Docs weren't trained
to recognize abuse, no one was

82
00:04:44,239 --> 00:04:46,098
Like this would've
fallen through the cracks easy

83
00:04:46,098 --> 00:04:47,981
And we got another boy in the box

84
00:04:47,981 --> 00:04:49,776
No one ever came forward
to claim him

85
00:04:49,776 --> 00:04:53,642
Back then they didn't have
facial reconstuction technology

86
00:04:53,642 --> 00:04:54,966
We do

87
00:04:54,966 --> 00:04:58,483
So we create a picture of what the victim
could have looked like off the skull

88
00:04:58,483 --> 00:05:00,070
Put this picture in circulation,
maybe an old neighbor

89
00:05:00,070 --> 00:05:04,441
or family member recognizes
baby Jane Doe

90
00:05:04,441 --> 00:05:08,263
Needle in a haystack but I might've
tracked your victim's fractures

91
00:05:08,263 --> 00:05:11,258
Two breaks on the forearm,
real unique injury, right?

92
00:05:11,258 --> 00:05:15,309
Same kind of breaks were treated at St
Boniface's emergency room circa 1965

93
00:05:15,309 --> 00:05:16,686
Did it say who the victim was?

94
00:05:16,686 --> 00:05:20,110
Vivian Smith, age 4, white female

95
00:05:20,110 --> 00:05:23,165
Doc who treated her,
still alive and kickin'

96
00:05:25,379 --> 00:05:27,249
Yes, that's my signature

97
00:05:27,249 --> 00:05:30,295
I was in my first year of
residency in '65

98
00:05:30,295 --> 00:05:32,268
Do you remember
that patient Dr Greys?

99
00:05:32,268 --> 00:05:35,418
Vivian Smith, 4 years old, white female

100
00:05:35,418 --> 00:05:39,182
Multiple fractures to the radius, ulna

101
00:05:39,182 --> 00:05:42,192
Yes I remember her

102
00:05:42,192 --> 00:05:45,862
First time I realized how little I could
do for children like that

103
00:05:45,862 --> 00:05:47,319
What d'you mean?

104
00:05:47,319 --> 00:05:50,750
I patch 'em up,
send them home untill the next time

105
00:05:50,750 --> 00:05:53,906
We think she was killed
shortly after you treated her

106
00:05:53,906 --> 00:05:56,076
Any idea who might've
been responsible?

107
00:05:56,076 --> 00:05:58,856
Mom
She brought her in

108
00:05:58,856 --> 00:06:00,859
A local waitress from
what I can remember

109
00:06:00,859 --> 00:06:02,633
Is there a father in the picture?

110
00:06:02,633 --> 00:06:04,516
According to this,

111
00:06:04,516 --> 00:06:08,682
Mom kept insisting
she dropped her kid

112
00:06:09,750 --> 00:06:12,571
It just happened so fast,
I was holding her

113
00:06:12,571 --> 00:06:15,013
and then next thing you know,
I dropped her

114
00:06:15,013 --> 00:06:17,638
Dropped her, huh?
How'd that happen?

115
00:06:17,638 --> 00:06:19,410
You dropping her?

116
00:06:19,410 --> 00:06:22,318
Silly me, I think I need glasses

117
00:06:22,318 --> 00:06:25,813
See my eyes they don't  work so hot
and I just keep dropping things

118
00:06:25,813 --> 00:06:27,783
Your daughter has spiral fractures

119
00:06:27,783 --> 00:06:31,940
It's caused when you take
a child's arm and snap it

120
00:06:35,667 --> 00:06:37,099
Take her away

121
00:06:37,099 --> 00:06:38,459
Excuse me?

122
00:06:38,459 --> 00:06:40,493
She's better off without me

123
00:06:40,493 --> 00:06:42,886
What about your mother's?
Or a relative's?

124
00:06:42,886 --> 00:06:45,467
I don't have anyone

125
00:06:45,467 --> 00:06:49,990
Please, just take her away
before it's too late

126
00:06:52,760 --> 00:06:55,901
I can't just take your kid

127
00:06:55,901 --> 00:06:58,839
You wanna get those eyes looked at

128
00:06:58,839 --> 00:07:01,896
Sign for your daughter here

129
00:07:04,982 --> 00:07:07,498
So Mom was trying to
save the kid from herself?

130
00:07:07,498 --> 00:07:08,838
There was nothing I could do

131
00:07:08,838 --> 00:07:12,113
Child abuse wasn't even
a concept in '65

132
00:07:12,113 --> 00:07:14,636
Anyway Mom gave us a false name

133
00:07:14,636 --> 00:07:16,226
How did you know that?

134
00:07:16,226 --> 00:07:18,463
Hospital bill came back a week later

135
00:07:18,463 --> 00:07:21,121
No known recipient
No known address

136
00:07:21,121 --> 00:07:23,679
You said she was a local girl?
A waitress?

137
00:07:23,679 --> 00:07:25,257
Car-hop kind of uniform?

138
00:07:25,257 --> 00:07:26,956
That's what it looked like

139
00:07:26,956 --> 00:07:29,113
The only car-hop in Philly
is Milt's Burger Joint

140
00:07:29,113 --> 00:07:30,490
Thurman Street

141
00:07:30,490 --> 00:07:33,149
Best cheese fries in town

142
00:07:39,444 --> 00:07:42,483
Place was a car-hop back in '65

143
00:07:42,483 --> 00:07:44,389
You worked here as
a waitress, Madi?

144
00:07:44,389 --> 00:07:49,118
Scrimped and saved my tips for years
'til I could call this armpit my home

145
00:07:49,118 --> 00:07:53,712
You remeber another waitress?
Had a daughter 4 years old

146
00:07:53,712 --> 00:07:57,256
Kid might've had a cast
on her arm

147
00:07:57,256 --> 00:08:01,563
Sure
Cindysomething

148
00:08:01,563 --> 00:08:03,499
I don't recall her last name

149
00:08:03,499 --> 00:08:05,501
Well maybe we'll have a talk
with the former owner

150
00:08:05,501 --> 00:08:07,128
Good luck

151
00:08:07,128 --> 00:08:13,429
Cheap pervert took a nose dive
into his cheese fries 10 years back

152
00:08:14,311 --> 00:08:17,274
What do you remember
about this Cindy?

153
00:08:17,274 --> 00:08:19,479
Restless skittish kind of gal

154
00:08:19,479 --> 00:08:20,699
The type who had it all

155
00:08:20,699 --> 00:08:23,372
Great husband, great kid

156
00:08:23,372 --> 00:08:24,743
Wanted nothing to do with 'em

157
00:08:24,743 --> 00:08:26,619
She was married?

158
00:08:27,365 --> 00:08:29,188
Met her husband once

159
00:08:29,188 --> 00:08:32,031
Heart of gold type, but her,

160
00:08:32,031 --> 00:08:36,176
something was rotten
up in the old spaghetti factory

161
00:08:56,513 --> 00:08:58,684
You get used to it honey

162
00:08:58,684 --> 00:09:02,299
How much money does it take to

163
00:09:02,299 --> 00:09:04,662
- run away?
- Run away?

164
00:09:04,662 --> 00:09:06,373
What would you want to
run away for, honey?

165
00:09:06,373 --> 00:09:08,824
Don't you have a family?

166
00:09:08,824 --> 00:09:11,025
I'm a bad mother

167
00:09:11,025 --> 00:09:13,201
Oh, you don't mean that now

168
00:09:13,201 --> 00:09:17,954
Sometimes I think my only way out is
when one of them dies

169
00:09:18,799 --> 00:09:20,960
Sweetheart?

170
00:09:23,416 --> 00:09:24,928
What are you doing here, Roger?

171
00:09:24,928 --> 00:09:26,717
Why aren't you at work?

172
00:09:26,717 --> 00:09:30,283
- I went to see my girls
- Mommy, mommy!

173
00:09:30,283 --> 00:09:32,813
Look what daddy got me!

174
00:09:32,813 --> 00:09:35,553
Oh, Vivian, she's beautiful

175
00:09:35,553 --> 00:09:40,018
I got a white paw just like Snowflake

176
00:09:41,615 --> 00:09:46,308
Stay in the car sweetie,
let Mommy and Daddy talk

177
00:09:46,308 --> 00:09:48,944
She's gonna be OK, Cindy

178
00:09:48,944 --> 00:09:50,572
How can you say that?

179
00:09:50,572 --> 00:09:53,530
The most important thing
is that we work this out

180
00:09:53,530 --> 00:09:55,880
As a family

181
00:09:55,880 --> 00:10:00,118
- I can't
- You're her Mommy

182
00:10:00,118 --> 00:10:04,124
Nothing's ever gonna change that

183
00:10:04,124 --> 00:10:06,574
She needs you

184
00:10:07,168 --> 00:10:09,965
I need you

185
00:10:18,235 --> 00:10:21,514
Had that man wrapped
around her little finger

186
00:10:21,514 --> 00:10:24,350
Sounds like she was about to bolt,

187
00:10:24,350 --> 00:10:26,305
and he was desperate to keep her

188
00:10:26,305 --> 00:10:30,459
- At any cost
- Lil, boss called

189
00:10:30,459 --> 00:10:33,191
Thanks for your time, Madi

190
00:10:33,727 --> 00:10:36,674
They put those facial reconstuction
photos of baby Jane Doe out

191
00:10:36,674 --> 00:10:38,142
- That was fast
- Got a hit

192
00:10:38,142 --> 00:10:41,969
Lady came in 5 minutes ago,
says she knows our girl

193
00:10:46,472 --> 00:10:49,806
I was just leaving the courthouse
when I saw this

194
00:10:50,226 --> 00:10:52,707
You work at the PD's office,
Miss Stanton?

195
00:10:52,707 --> 00:10:54,144
Court reporter

196
00:10:54,144 --> 00:10:55,768
Are you saying you know this girl?

197
00:10:55,768 --> 00:10:58,981
No I mean yes, I think I do

198
00:10:58,981 --> 00:11:02,556
- Can I ask a question?
- Sure

199
00:11:02,556 --> 00:11:06,810
- Rumor has it you found her in the river
- Yes, we did

200
00:11:06,810 --> 00:11:09,404
How did she die?

201
00:11:09,975 --> 00:11:12,608
We're not sure yet

202
00:11:12,608 --> 00:11:15,449
Anyway, cut to the chase

203
00:11:21,010 --> 00:11:22,425
It's a pretty close match

204
00:11:22,425 --> 00:11:24,262
Where'd you get this photo?

205
00:11:24,262 --> 00:11:26,749
It's one of the few things
I have left from my childhood

206
00:11:26,749 --> 00:11:28,180
How do you mean?

207
00:11:28,180 --> 00:11:34,096
That little girl in the photo,
that girl is me

208
00:11:39,434 --> 00:11:41,943
I was adopted when I was 4

209
00:11:41,943 --> 00:11:44,720
There's very little I remember
before then

210
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:47,496
But I always felt a part of me
was missing

211
00:11:47,496 --> 00:11:51,141
Do you remember her at all?

212
00:11:51,645 --> 00:11:56,017
I remember a girl but
I thought she was my invisible friend

213
00:11:56,017 --> 00:11:59,426
Something a child makes up,
I never thought she could be real

214
00:11:59,426 --> 00:12:01,299
Well we'll need to take a swab

215
00:12:01,299 --> 00:12:04,471
Test your DNA against our
baby Jane Doe

216
00:12:04,471 --> 00:12:07,824
So the girl you found in the river,

217
00:12:07,824 --> 00:12:12,248
- she could've been my sister
- It's possible

218
00:12:12,248 --> 00:12:16,522
What about your parents?
Do you remember them?

219
00:12:17,640 --> 00:12:20,266
Last time I saw my mother,

220
00:12:20,956 --> 00:12:24,581
that's the only memory I have

221
00:12:36,561 --> 00:12:39,500
Where's Vivian, Mommy?

222
00:12:40,540 --> 00:12:42,952
Listen to me, sweetheart

223
00:12:42,952 --> 00:12:47,248
Vivian, she's just someone
you made up in your mind

224
00:12:47,248 --> 00:12:50,069
Like an invisible friend

225
00:12:50,069 --> 00:12:52,811
Vivian's just make believe?

226
00:12:52,811 --> 00:12:54,477
Don't you see?

227
00:12:54,477 --> 00:12:56,467
It's so much better this way,

228
00:12:56,467 --> 00:12:58,504
because she'll always be with you

229
00:12:58,504 --> 00:13:01,441
Watching over you
no matter where you go

230
00:13:01,441 --> 00:13:04,072
Like an angel?

231
00:13:05,477 --> 00:13:10,035
Yes Like an angel

232
00:13:10,035 --> 00:13:12,144
Go to sleep now, sweetheart

233
00:13:12,144 --> 00:13:14,987
Close your eyes

234
00:13:17,938 --> 00:13:21,013
You'll be in good hands here

235
00:13:21,013 --> 00:13:24,404
Better off without me

236
00:13:24,404 --> 00:13:26,616
He'll keep you safe

237
00:13:26,616 --> 00:13:30,371
And whenever it seems
Mommy's far, far away,

238
00:13:30,371 --> 00:13:33,084
all you have to do
is close your eyes

239
00:13:33,084 --> 00:13:36,186
And I'll be here with you

240
00:13:43,424 --> 00:13:45,945
Forever?

241
00:13:45,945 --> 00:13:48,377
And ever

242
00:13:49,904 --> 00:13:53,748
Bye-bye, baby

243
00:13:56,749 --> 00:13:59,194
I never saw her again

244
00:13:59,194 --> 00:14:01,347
DHS found me a home

245
00:14:01,347 --> 00:14:03,524
Good loving people raised me,
I was lucky

246
00:14:03,524 --> 00:14:06,242
That medallion your mother gave you,

247
00:14:06,242 --> 00:14:09,520
- do you still have it?
- I do, yeah

248
00:14:13,539 --> 00:14:16,242
She mentioned a man
watching over you,

249
00:14:16,242 --> 00:14:18,648
he'll keep you safe, she said

250
00:14:18,648 --> 00:14:22,938
St Michael, maybe
that's what she meant

251
00:14:24,352 --> 00:14:26,792
BN 3546

252
00:14:26,792 --> 00:14:28,946
I always wondered
what that meant

253
00:14:28,946 --> 00:14:31,724
St Michael's the patron saint of cops

254
00:14:31,724 --> 00:14:35,883
BN could mean badge number

255
00:14:36,482 --> 00:14:39,460
I'll let you know
if there's something to it more

256
00:14:39,460 --> 00:14:41,189
Thanks for your time

257
00:14:41,189 --> 00:14:43,310
I've had a good life

258
00:14:43,310 --> 00:14:49,234
But still I'd like to know

259
00:14:49,234 --> 00:14:52,606
Why she left

260
00:14:59,330 --> 00:15:01,495
Art Balduchi?

261
00:15:03,588 --> 00:15:06,052
No need to shine them badges

262
00:15:06,052 --> 00:15:08,000
Cheery mugs give you boys away

263
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:10,042
Takes a cop to know a cop

264
00:15:10,042 --> 00:15:12,106
Badge number 3546

